Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Description", "Section",
 Editable->False,
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8242782643101068`*^9, 
  3.824278284056035*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"20c3f844-488c-4c14-8ab7-\
9b472d3f07f2"],

Cell["\<\
This Demonstration shows plots of various diagnostic accuracy measures for \
diagnostic tests in normally distributed nondiseased and diseased \
populations. This is done for different values of disease prevalence, taking \
into account the means and standard deviations of the populations. The means \
and standard deviations are expressed in arbitrary units. The measures \
considered are the positive predictive value (PPV), the negative predictive \
value (NPV), the (diagnostic) odds ratio (OR), the likelihood ratio for a \
positive test result (LR+), and the likelihood ratio for a negative test \
result (LR-). The measures are plotted against the sensitivity (Se) or the \
specificity (Sp) of the test, which can be selected by clicking the \
respective button.\
\>", "Text",
 Editable->False,
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.646298043261019*^9, 3.646298190185018*^9}, 
   3.6462991089650187`*^9, {3.6463088013578854`*^9, 3.6463088128778853`*^9}, {
