Cell[TextData[{
 "The measures that are used in the evaluation of the clinical accuracy of a \
diagnostic test applied to a diseased or nondiseased population can be \
calculated as functions of the sensitivity or the specificity of the test. \
Sensitivity is the fraction of the diseased population with a positive test \
result, while specificity is the fraction of the nondiseased population with \
a negative test result. If we denote by ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["v", TraditionalForm]], "InlineMath",
  FontSlant->"Plain",ExpressionUUID->"895f9428-97c9-5943-9063-6263c2032364"],
 " the disease prevalence, we have: "
}], "Text",
 Editable->False,
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.6462972184250193`*^9, {3.646299017067019*^9, 3.646299034809018*^9}, {
   3.6464175360817204`*^9, 3.646417617296505*^9}, {3.646503135886409*^9, 
   3.646503162726223*^9}, {3.646503204507545*^9, 3.6465032210780993`*^9}, 
   3.646503453674555*^9, {3.646590274420603*^9, 3.646590286439289*^9}, {
